          <h1><a href="whats-new-at-curbee-spring-2026-product-updates%3FhsLang=en.html">Curbee Spring 2026 Product Update</a></h1>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
          <span> Written by <a class="author-link" href="author/curbee%3FhsLang=en.html">Curbee</a> | June 12, 2026 </span>
        </div>
        <div class="blog-section">
          <span><p><span>Mobile service already helps teams meet customers where they are. And now, Curbee is getting even better at supporting everything that happens before, during, and after each driveway visit.</span></p>
<p><span>From scheduling and service areas to reminders, technician updates, weather-aware planning, and customer communications, our latest product updates are designed to make the mobile service experience even smoother, smarter, and easier to manage.</span></p>
<p><span>Because when the behind-the-scenes coordination feels effortless, teams can stay focused on what matters most: delivering a great customer experience.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><span>Here’s what’s new.</span></p>
<h3><strong><span>Customers Now Know When Help Is on the Way</span></strong></h3>
<p><span>No one likes wondering when someone will arrive. Especially when that “someone” is coming to service your vehicle.</span></p>
<p><span>Curbee now supports automated </span><strong><span>On the Way</span></strong><span> and </span><strong><span>Arrived</span></strong><span> notifications, so customers get timely updates when their technician is headed over and when they’ve arrived.</span></p>
<p><span><amp-img src="/blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png?width=449&amp;height=449&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png" width="449" height="449" alt="Product Updates  June 2026 (5)" srcset="/blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png?width=225&amp;height=225&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png 225w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png?width=449&amp;height=449&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png 449w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png?width=674&amp;height=674&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png 674w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png?width=898&amp;height=898&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png 898w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png?width=1123&amp;height=1123&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png 1123w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png?width=1347&amp;height=1347&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(5).png 1347w" layout="responsive"></amp-img></span></p>
<p><span>The best part? These updates are triggered directly from the technician’s status in the Crew App, which means communication stays accurate, consistent, and easy for your team.</span></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span>Customers get peace of mind.</span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><span></span><span>Dealership teams get fewer “Where’s my technician?” calls.</span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><span></span><span>Everybody wins.</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span>And when technician photos are added, customers can also see who’s coming before they arrive — a small touch that helps build trust before the first knock on the door.</span></p>
<h3><strong><span>The Crew App Just Got a Serious Upgrade</span></strong></h3>
<p><span>Technicians are already out in the field doing the work. Now, they can even book appointments right on the spot from the Crew App.</span></p>
<p><span>With the <span>new Appointments experience</span>, technicians can:</span></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span>View upcoming appointments by day and service vehicle</span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><span></span><span>Search for appointments by customer name, email, phone number, or VIN</span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><span></span><span>Book new appointments while they’re on-site</span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><span></span><span>Add notes for future visits and better team coordination</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span><amp-img src="/blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png?width=768&amp;height=272&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png" width="768" height="272" alt="Product Updates  June 2026 (3)" srcset="/blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png?width=384&amp;height=136&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png 384w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png?width=768&amp;height=272&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png 768w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png?width=1152&amp;height=408&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png 1152w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png?width=1536&amp;height=544&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png 1536w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png?width=1920&amp;height=680&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png 1920w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png?width=2304&amp;height=816&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(3).png 2304w" layout="responsive"></amp-img></span><span>That means fewer handoffs, faster follow-up scheduling, and more control in the hands of the people closest to the customer.</span></p>
<p><span>Think of it as giving your mobile service team a command center that fits in their pocket.</span></p>
<h3><strong><span>Service Areas Are Now Easier to See</span></strong></h3>
<p><span>Service area rules have always been working behind the scenes. Now, your team can actually see them.</span></p>
<p><span>In Map View, users can turn on a <span>service area toggle </span>for a specific service vehicle and date. This gives your team a clear visual of where that vehicle can perform mobile service.</span></p>
<p><span>It’s especially useful when answering questions like:</span></p>
<p><span>“Do we cover this address?”</span><span><br></span><span>“Why can’t this location be booked?”</span><span><br></span><span>“Which areas are available for this vehicle on this day?”</span></p>
<p><span><amp-img src="/blog/hs-fs/hubfs/3-2.png?width=670&amp;height=335&amp;name=3-2.png" width="670" height="335" alt="3-2" srcset="/blog/hs-fs/hubfs/3-2.png?width=335&amp;height=168&amp;name=3-2.png 335w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/3-2.png?width=670&amp;height=335&amp;name=3-2.png 670w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/3-2.png?width=1005&amp;height=503&amp;name=3-2.png 1005w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/3-2.png?width=1340&amp;height=670&amp;name=3-2.png 1340w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/3-2.png?width=1675&amp;height=838&amp;name=3-2.png 1675w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/3-2.png?width=2010&amp;height=1005&amp;name=3-2.png 2010w" layout="responsive"></amp-img></span></p>
<p><span>No guessing. No hunting. Just a clearer view of your coverage.</span></p>
<h3><strong><span>Customers Can Add Appointments to Their Calendar</span></strong></h3>
<p><span>Mobile service appointments are often booked days, weeks, or even months in advance. And customers are busy. Calendars help.</span></p>
<p><span>Now, confirmation emails include </span><strong><span>Add to Calendar</span></strong><span> options for Google Calendar, Apple Calendar, Outlook, and other calendar tools. Customers can save the appointment right away and get reminders from the calendar they already use.</span></p>
<p><span><amp-img src="/blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png?width=636&amp;height=318&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png" width="636" height="318" alt="Product Updates  June 2026" srcset="/blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png?width=318&amp;height=159&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png 318w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png?width=636&amp;height=318&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png 636w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png?width=954&amp;height=477&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png 954w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png?width=1272&amp;height=636&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png 1272w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png?width=1590&amp;height=795&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png 1590w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png?width=1908&amp;height=954&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026.png 1908w" layout="responsive"></amp-img></span></p>
<p><span>It’s a simple upgrade that helps appointments stay remembered, not buried in an inbox.</span></p>
<h3><strong><span>Appointment Maps Got More Useful</span></strong></h3>
<p><span>The appointment confirmation map is no longer just a static image.</span></p>
<p><span>Users can now <span>zoom, pan, and switch between Satellite, Map, and Terrain views</span> while reviewing an appointment location.</span></p>
<p><span><amp-img src="/blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png?width=566&amp;height=424&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png" width="566" height="424" alt="Product Updates  June 2026 (4)" srcset="/blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png?width=283&amp;height=212&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png 283w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png?width=566&amp;height=424&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png 566w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png?width=849&amp;height=636&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png 849w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png?width=1132&amp;height=848&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png 1132w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png?width=1415&amp;height=1060&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png 1415w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png?width=1698&amp;height=1272&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(4).png 1698w" layout="responsive"></amp-img></span></p>
<p><span>That means more context before the appointment is finalized — whether your team is checking the exact address, looking at the surrounding area, or adding helpful notes about access, parking, gates, or where the technician should go.</span></p>
<p><span>Tiny map. Big help.</span></p>
<h3><strong><span>Weather Is Now Part of the Scheduling Conversation</span></strong></h3>
<p><span>Weather can make or break a mobile service day.</span></p>
<p><span>Curbee now shows forecast information directly on the <span>Date &amp; Time selection screen</span> during booking. The forecast is based on the customer’s appointment address and updates automatically if the address changes.</span></p>
<p><span>Your team can see helpful details like temperature, general conditions, precipitation, wind, humidity, and more.</span></p>
<p><span><amp-img src="/blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png?width=478&amp;height=478&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png" width="478" height="478" alt="Product Updates  June 2026 (2)" srcset="/blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png?width=239&amp;height=239&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png 239w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png?width=478&amp;height=478&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png 478w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png?width=717&amp;height=717&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png 717w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png?width=956&amp;height=956&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png 956w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png?width=1195&amp;height=1195&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png 1195w, /blog/hs-fs/hubfs/Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png?width=1434&amp;height=1434&amp;name=Product%20Updates%20%20June%202026%20(2).png 1434w" layout="responsive"></amp-img></span></p>
<p><span>It won’t block anyone from booking, but it does give teams better visibility so they can plan smarter and avoid avoidable surprises.</span></p>
<p><span>Because nobody wants to discover a thunderstorm after the appointment is already on the schedule.</span></p>
<h3><strong><span>Future Appointments Get an Extra Reminder</span></strong></h3>
<p><span>As more teams book follow-up service further in advance, customers need a little extra help remembering what’s ahead.</span></p>
<p><span>Curbee now sends an<span> automatic reminder email</span> two weeks before eligible appointments. This is in addition to the existing reminder sent the night before the appointment.</span></p>
<p><span>That gives customers more time to remember, prepare, or reschedule if needed — and gives your team a better shot at keeping the day running smoothly.</span></p>
<h3><strong><span>Built for Our Partners</span></strong></h3>
<p><span>Together, these updates are designed to make mobile service feel more connected from start to finish.</span></p>
<p><span>Customers get better communication and easier reminders.</span></p>
<p><span></span><span></span><span>Technicians get more tools in the field.</span></p>
<p><span>Dealership teams get more visibility into appointments, service areas, locations, and weather.</span></p>
<p><span>It all adds up to a smoother experience before, during, and after every mobile service visit.</span></p>
<p><span>And that’s exactly what Curbee is here to help dealerships do: deliver mobile service that feels easy, modern, and on the move.</span></p>

